ABO WGS - 1000 Genomes 30x on GRCH38

Jonathan Stevens

1000 Genomes 30x on GRCH38

1000 Genomes 30x on GRCH38 (Byrska-Bishop et al. 2021) data set was obtained from https://www.internationalgenome.org/data-portal/data-collection/30x-grch38. The cram files were downloaded and filtered for the ABO gene using samtools (Li et al. 2009) view and coordinates chr9:133255176-133385146.

# example usage of samtools view command
samtools view -h -C -T ../ref/Homo_sapiens_assembly38.fasta     ftp://ftp.sra.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/run/ERR323/ERR3239484/NA12778.final.cram    chr9:133255176-133385146 >     NA12778.extract_for_bloodantigens-full_gene_master.cram

1.1 ABO gene sequence depth

depth.sh was used to iterate over all cram files in the directory, process with samtools depth, and output depth file per sample.

# example usage of samtools depth command for one sample cram
# -a (all positions), -r (specified region)
samtools depth -a -r chr9:133255176-133385146 /Users/jonathan_stevens/ABO/1000G_data/cram/HG00096.extract_for_bloodantigens-full_gene_master.cram -o /Users/jonathan_stevens/ABO/1000G_data/depth/HG00096_ABO_pos_read_depth_of_coverage.txt

The depth command creates a tab separated file (sample_ABO_pos_read_depth_of_coverage.txt) containing chromosome, position, and depth:

## chr9 133255176   94
## chr9 133255177   96
## chr9 133255178   96
## chr9 133255179   95
## chr9 133255180   96
## ...

1.1.1 Average depth per 100 base interval

coverage_per_interval_ABO.py was used to iterate over the depth files in a directory and write the average sequence depth of each sample per 100 base interval to a tab delimited text file (1000G_100bp_avg_read_depth_of_coverage.txt).

1.2 ABO gene sequence copy number

copy_number_per_interval.py was used to iterate over depth files in a directory and write the average copy number of each sample per 100 base interval to a tab delimited text file (1000G_100bp_avg_copy_number.txt). The text file was formatted in Excel with conditional highlighting to visualize copy number (1000G_100bp_avg_copy_number.xlsx).

copy_number_per_region.py - iterate over depth files in a directory and write the average copy number gene region (UTRs, exons, introns) to a tab delimited text file (copy_number_per_region.txt). The text file was formatted in Excel with conditional highlighting to visualize copy number (copy_number_per_region.xlsx).

2. VCF Analysis

2.1 Genotype VCF (nonphased) analysis

The nonphased chromosome 9 VCF file and index were obtained from https://www.internationalgenome.org/data-portal/data-collection/30x-grch38.

curl -C - -O ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/data_collections/1000G_2504_high_coverage/working/20201028_3202_raw_GT_with_annot/20201028_CCDG_14151_B01_GRM_WGS_2020-08-05_chr9.recalibrated_variants.vcf.gz

curl -C - -O ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/data_collections/1000G_2504_high_coverage/working/20201028_3202_raw_GT_with_annot/20201028_CCDG_14151_B01_GRM_WGS_2020-08-05_chr9.recalibrated_variants.vcf.gz.tbi

vcftools (P. Danecek et al. 2011) was used to extract the ABO gene using coordinates 133246000-133320000 and write to a new VCF.

vcftools --gzvcf 20201028_CCDG_14151_B01_GRM_WGS_2020-08-05_chr9.recalibrated_variants.vcf.gz --out chr9_ABO.recalibrated_variants --chr chr9 --from-bp 133246000 --to-bp 133320000 --recode

2.1.1 Full sequence variants

bcftools (Petr Danecek et al. 2021) query was used to create a tab separated file containing the variant genotype calls translated to IUPAC codes.

bcftools query -f '%POS[\t%IUPACGT]\n' -H -o ABO_vcf_table.txt chr9_ABO.recalibrated.variants.recode.vcf

transpose_table.py was used to read ABO_vcf_table.txt as a pandas dataframe, transpose the dataframe, and write the dataframe to a new text file, ABO_vcf_table_transposed.txt

reverse_complement.py was used to reverse complement the data in ABO_vcf_table_transposed.txt and write to a new file, ABO_vcf_table_transposed_reverse_complement.txt.

2.1.2 CDS variants

bcftools query was used to create a tab separated file containing the variant genotype calls translated to IUPAC codes for the coding sequence. The -R (–regions-file) command was used with a BED file containing exon coordinates. This command required the bgzipped VCF and associated tabix index.

# bgzip VCF file
bgzip chr9_ABO.recalibrated_variants.recode.vcf
# index .vcf.gz file
bcftools index -t chr9_ABO.recalibrated_variants.recode.vcf.gz
# query regions for CDS and write to tab delimited file, ABO_vcf_table_CDS.txt
bcftools query -R ABO.bed -f '%POS[\t%IUPACGT]\n' -H -o ABO_vcf_table_CDS.txt chr9_ABO.recalibrated_variants.recode.vcf.gz

transpose_table.py was used to read ABO_vcf_table_CDS.txt as a pandas dataframe, transpose the dataframe, and write the dataframe to a new text file, ABO_vcf_table_CDS_transposed.txt

reverse_complement.py was used to reverse complement the data in ABO_vcf_table_CDS_transposed.txt and write to a new file, ABO_vcf_table_CDS_transposed_reverse_complement.txt.

2.2 Genotype VCF (phased) analysis

The phased chromosome 9 VCF file and index were obtained from https://www.internationalgenome.org/data-portal/data-collection/30x-grch38.

curl -C - -O ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/data_collections/1000G_2504_high_coverage/working/20201028_3202_phased/CCDG_14151_B01_GRM_WGS_2020-08-05_chr9.filtered.shapeit2-duohmm-phased.vcf.gz
 
curl -C - -O ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk/vol1/ftp/data_collections/1000G_2504_high_coverage/working/20201028_3202_phased/CCDG_14151_B01_GRM_WGS_2020-08-05_chr9.filtered.shapeit2-duohmm-phased.vcf.gz.tbi
vcftools --gzvcf CCDG_14151_B01_GRM_WGS_2020-08-05_chr9.filtered.shapeit2-duohmm-phased.vcf.gz --out chr9_ABO.filtered.shapeit2-duohmm-phased --chr chr9 --from-bp 133246000 --to-bp 133320000 --recode
